M||tx|---
M||titl|Use after() for Non-Blocking Operations
M||impa|md
M||impa|faster rp times
M||tags|server, async, logging, an, side-effects
M||tx|---
M|Use |tx|Use nx.js's `after()` to schedule work that shd execute after a rp is sent. This prevents logging, an, and other side effects from blocking the rp.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|import { logUserAction } from '@/app/utils'
M|Use |expo|Request) {
M|Use |tx|// Perform mutation
M|Use |tx|await updateDatabase(request)
M|Use |tx|// Logging blocks the rp
M|Use |tx|const userAgent = request.headers.get('us-ag') \|\| 'unknown'
M|Use |tx|await logUserAction({ userAgent })
M|Use |retu|'sc' }), {
M|Use |stat|200,
M|Use |head|{ 'cn-tp': 'application/json' }
M|Use |tx|})
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|import { after } from 'nx/server'
M|Use |tx|import { headers, cookies } from 'nx/headers'
M|Use |tx|import { logUserAction } from '@/app/utils'
M|Use |expo|Request) {
M|Use |tx|// Perform mutation
M|Use |tx|await updateDatabase(request)
M|Use |tx|// Log after rp is sent
M|Use |tx|after(async () => {
M|Use |tx|const userAgent = (await headers()).get('us-ag') \|\| 'unknown'
M|Use |tx|const sessionCookie = (await cookies()).get('sn-id')?.value \|\| 'anonymous'
M|Use |tx|logUserAction({ sessionCookie, userAgent })
M|Use |tx|})
M|Use |retu|'sc' }), {
M|Use |stat|200,
M|Use |head|{ 'cn-tp': 'application/json' }
M|Use |tx|})
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |tx|The rp is sent immediately while logging happens in the background.
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |it|an tracking
M|Use |it|Audit logging
M|Use |it|Sending notifications
M|Use |it|Cache invalidation
M|Use |it|Cleanup tasks
M|Use |**Im|**
M|Use |it|`after()` runs even if the rp fails or redirects
M|Use |it|Works in Server Actions, rt Handlers, and Server cp
